# Suricata config changes (lab)

File edited:
- `/etc/suricata/suricata.yaml`

## 1) Capture interface (AF-PACKET)
Reason: Ubuntu has multiple interfaces; this lab uses `ens34` (192.168.28.128)

```yaml
af-packet:
  - interface: ens34
    cluster-id: 99
    cluster-type: cluster_flow
    defrag: yes
```

## 2) EVE JSON output enabled
Reason: Send structured telemetry to Splunk from /var/log/suricata/eve.json

```yaml
outputs:
  - eve-log:
      enabled: yes
      filetype: regular
      filename: /var/log/suricata/eve.json
      types:
        - flow
        - alert
        - dns
        - http
        - tls
```

## 3) Rules path + rule file
Reason: Load downloaded ruleset via suricata-update.

```bash
default-rule-path: /var/lib/suricata/rules

rule-files:
  - suricata.rules
```

## 4) Validation commands

```yaml
sudo suricata-update
sudo suricata -T -c /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml -v
sudo systemctl restart suricata
sudo systemctl status suricata --no-pager
```

## 5) Verify log keluar

```bash
sudo tail -n 50 /var/log/suricata/eve.json
sudo tail -n 500 /var/log/suricata/eve.json | grep '"event_type":"flow"' | tail
```
